abstract: Swiss voters back moderate parties in their general election and nationalist Swiss People's Party loses ground after mounting a campaign heavy on anti-immigrant sentiment; results halt 20 years of steady growth by the People's Party in parliamentary elections.
snippet: The People’s Party, which supports an anti-immigrant platform, won the most votes, although it dropped from its results four years ago.
lead_paragraph: The People’s Party, which supports an anti-immigrant platform, won the most votes, although it dropped from its results four years ago.
